548
00:48:24,099 --> 00:48:33,828
And this resolution is focused on a short end time frame put forth to address the need of charter review.

549
00:48:34,588 --> 00:48:36,310
So this is a very focused plan.

550
00:48:36,975 --> 00:48:50,620
that this is just the first step, and I hope many steps, to get input from the public and craft a home rule petition that eventually will go to the state legislature for approval.

551
00:48:51,180 --> 00:49:03,244
So, I'd like to give just a little background, if I could, and then I know there are a number of people that would like to speak on this issue, and I look forward to the comments that are made tonight, Mr. President.

552
00:49:04,100 --> 00:49:11,563
A city charter is the constitution governing the municipal government that defines the powers the citizens agree to give their city government.

553
00:49:12,464 --> 00:49:23,789
The charter defines which officials are elected, their term lengths, duties, powers, and responsibilities, and establishes the lines of authority for city departments.

554
00:49:25,150 --> 00:49:31,353
Our current city charter calls for a modified Plan A form of government, which was approved under Chapter 605

555
00:49:33,078 --> 00:49:36,800
of the Acts of 1986, some 29 years ago.

556
00:49:38,121 --> 00:49:54,670
Once a community has a charter, there is often a provision for the periodic appointment of a charter review committee, whose purpose will be to conduct an examination of the city charter to determine the charter's ongoing utility and accuracy.

557
00:49:56,010 --> 00:49:59,752
In the case of our charter, no such provision currently exists.

558
00:50:01,013 --> 00:50:02,834
The intent of my resolution is to serve

559
00:50:03,456 --> 00:50:12,458
as a launching pad aimed at citizen-driven decision-making regarding how our city is governed, assuring that the charter is working as intended.

560
00:50:13,618 --> 00:50:22,621
I'm going to ask, Mr. President, after discussion, that this matter be sent to a Committee of the Whole meeting and that we meet within the next week.

561
00:50:23,501 --> 00:50:26,301
And the reason why I ask a week, Mr. President, I know we have a lot going on,

562
00:50:28,931 --> 00:50:35,755
get this on the ballot for this upcoming November election, and that is the election of a seven-member board.

563
00:50:36,135 --> 00:50:38,116
We're under certain time constraints.

564
00:50:38,877 --> 00:50:48,423
And so we have to meet, have a public hearing on this, where we can amend this particular resolution.

565
00:50:49,803 --> 00:50:53,165
Anyone familiar with how a home rule petition functions?

566
00:50:53,866 --> 00:50:57,448
It typically is originated by the mayor, the executive branch.

567
00:50:57,781 --> 00:51:00,903
And then it comes to the council, which is the legislative branch.

568
00:51:01,604 --> 00:51:19,336
