01:29:15,393 --> 01:29:15,913
To be clear,

962
01:29:17,670 --> 01:29:33,919
recent municipal election, why I think the mayor is on board with this, and I want to thank her too, is she won a very narrow election, and half of the city voted for Barpenta, who made it, I think, a forefront of his campaign.

963
01:29:34,359 --> 01:29:37,581
And with all due respect, I think that's why we're talking about it tonight.

964
01:29:38,301 --> 01:29:39,181
I just had to say that.

965
01:29:40,762 --> 01:29:45,585
I'm a little squeamish about this Collins, is that what it's called?

966
01:29:46,720 --> 01:29:48,300
call-in centre coming in.

967
01:29:49,041 --> 01:29:55,742
While I think we should definitely entertain any positive suggestions, this is for Medford.

968
01:29:56,162 --> 01:30:08,026
It should be driven by Medford residents, as former Councillor Camuso had once said when this was in discussion before when he was a member of this body, and I wholeheartedly agree with that.

969
01:30:08,666 --> 01:30:09,386
Without getting into

