03:08:06,938 --> 03:08:12,843
There's no, nobody's going to tell me right now which cameras are broken.

2244
03:08:12,903 --> 03:08:13,964
So I think it was, um,

2245
03:08:16,513 --> 03:08:23,256
brought up on Wednesday night that 10 to 14 percent of all cameras at the high school are broken.

2246
03:08:23,796 --> 03:08:28,159
I don't know the actual number.

2247
03:08:28,199 --> 03:08:29,739
That's kind of what I'm asking.

2248
03:08:29,799 --> 03:08:40,464
My issue with the whole situation is that there are cameras broken at the high school, and obviously we have the money or the school department has the money to fix it.

2249
03:08:40,544 --> 03:08:43,626
We just hired a public relations

2250
03:08:44,448 --> 03:08:49,231
or actually just implemented a new position, which is a public relations job, for $90,000.

2251
03:08:49,812 --> 03:08:59,518
So if we have money like that to hire and create new jobs, then we obviously have the money somewhere to fix the cameras that are broken.

2252
03:08:59,638 --> 03:09:00,759
I think that's necessary.

2253
03:09:00,959 --> 03:09:02,820
We put the cameras in for a reason.

2254
03:09:04,261 --> 03:09:09,065
If one or two are broken, they should be fixed, never mind 10% to 15% of the cameras being broken.

2255
03:09:16,300 --> 03:09:23,863
We're living in some times where, which is the reason why we put cameras in and around our high school.

2256
03:09:26,924 --> 03:09:36,228
I feel it's almost sad that so many are broken at this day and age.

2257
03:09:36,988 --> 03:09:42,230
So I would ask that we find out exactly how many are broken, if that is the true accurate figure.

2258
03:09:43,088 --> 03:09:45,630
how and when they're going to be fixed or replaced.

2259
03:09:49,652 --> 03:09:49,992
Thank you.

2260
03:09:50,012 --> 03:09:53,274
Mr. President, I want to thank Council Longo current for bringing this up.

2261
03:09:54,014 --> 03:10:03,740
Um, you know, it was mentioned that, uh, security at the high school in the past, I think it's five to eight years has been cut by 80% at one point back in, I think it was 2008.

2262
03:10:04,040 --> 03:10:07,862
Um, there were eight security guards at the high school.

2263
03:10:08,323 --> 03:10:12,245
There's currently one security guy at the high school and part of the reasoning

2264
03:10:12,958 --> 03:10:28,874
that were in committee reports is the fact that with the increase in technology, that the need to have security guards actually physically walking around the building, you know, this technology replaced the physical walking around the building.

2265
03:10:29,454 --> 03:10:31,917
And now what we're seeing is this technology

2266
03:10:32,307 --> 03:10:34,568
which the superintendent stated at the meeting.

2267
03:10:34,928 --> 03:10:35,668
I'm not stating.

2268
03:10:36,008 --> 03:10:44,330
The cameras that are on the outside of the buildings, not just the high school, around all the school buildings are not good in New England weather.

2269
03:10:44,890 --> 03:10:46,450
They're not good for New England weather.

2270
03:10:46,490 --> 03:10:48,471
He said this at an open public meeting.

2271
03:10:49,031 --> 03:10:54,512
So I'm not sure who was responsible for these cameras, but we happen to live in New England.

2272
03:10:55,334 --> 03:10:58,497
And you know, we happen to get snow and rain and wind like we got tonight.

2273
03:10:58,977 --> 03:11:04,482
So I'm not quite sure why these cameras and the numbers that were mentioned were percentages.

2274
03:11:04,982 --> 03:11:14,150
So it was the superintendent of school at a public meeting said 10% of the 144, I think he said 144, 145 cameras currently are not working.

2275
03:11:14,511 --> 03:11:21,897
