Thank you, Mr. Clerk.

2506
03:30:04,548 --> 03:30:11,251
If we could send that to the DBW for an answer.

2507
03:30:11,612 --> 03:30:12,312
All those in favor?

2508
03:30:13,833 --> 03:30:14,353
Motion passes.

2509
03:30:16,178 --> 03:30:29,888
Offered by Council of Ninth, be it resolved that the administration provide an update regarding Council Paper 15-523 regarding the probate status of 56 Boynton Road.

2510
03:30:30,268 --> 03:30:30,869
Council of Ninth.

2511
03:30:31,818 --> 03:30:34,019
Yes, Mr. President, this is an important neighborhood issue.

2512
03:30:34,039 --> 03:30:41,822
A number of residents came down and spoke out against the property at 56 Boynton Road, which is an abandoned and condemned property, Mr. President.

2513
03:30:41,862 --> 03:30:46,424
It's my understanding that the matter was going through probate court, probate litigation.

2514
03:30:46,524 --> 03:30:48,925
However, it seems like it's taking an inordinate amount of time.

2515
03:30:49,382 --> 03:30:51,223
for us to come to a resolve on this.

2516
03:30:51,323 --> 03:30:52,804
The building is a public nuisance.

2517
03:30:52,864 --> 03:30:54,744
The building is an eyesore in the neighborhood.

2518
03:30:55,845 --> 03:30:59,507
It is a calling card for animals of all types.

2519
03:30:59,967 --> 03:31:05,069
And it's my hope that we can get an update on this, Mr. President, because I think it's time that we need to move and take action.

2520
03:31:08,471 --> 03:31:09,051
Move approval.

2521
03:31:09,271 --> 03:31:09,591
Thank you.

2522
03:31:11,132 --> 03:31:17,835
Offered by Councilmember Kern, be it resolved that the still leaking roof at Bethel Public Library be discussed.

2523
03:31:21,089 --> 03:31:23,471
Thank you, President Carviello.

2524
03:31:23,491 --> 03:31:25,393
I would just like to bring this up.

2525
03:31:25,433 --> 03:31:27,255
I was in the library today with my daughter.

2526
03:31:28,095 --> 03:31:34,881
And the roof is not only leaking, but it's leaking in multiple spots.

2527
03:31:34,921 --> 03:31:42,208
And there's buckets in the children's section, catching water right almost near the movie section.

2528
03:31:42,388 --> 03:31:46,992
It's so bad that the carpet is, it seemed like the carpet was wet with the bucket.

2529
03:31:49,953 --> 03:31:52,314
I was obviously very frustrated.

2530
03:31:52,594 --> 03:31:54,575
We've discussed this a number of times.

2531
03:31:54,635 --> 03:31:59,797
You know, if you're at home and you hear a drip in your house, you call the roofing company immediately.

2532
03:31:59,817 --> 03:32:03,138
I feel like we've asked the administration to do that.

2533
03:32:03,218 --> 03:32:11,121
I know they were having somebody in to take a look and estimate, but that was probably about three, four weeks ago.

2534
03:32:11,641 --> 03:32:15,983
So I would just like an update, not only ask for an update,

2535
03:32:16,376 --> 03:32:18,016
you know, what the status is with the roof.

2536
03:32:18,056 --> 03:32:21,057
I'm not sure if any of my colleagues know what the status is.

2537
03:32:21,657 --> 03:32:26,438
I tried to talk to Barbara Kerr, but she wasn't in at the time.

2538
03:32:26,458 --> 03:32:28,938
I was right there early in the morning.

2539
03:32:29,558 --> 03:32:31,699
So number one, what's the status of the roof?

2540
03:32:32,099 --> 03:32:38,920
And number two, ask the administration to fix it immediately before it creates more of a problem.

2541
03:32:39,620 --> 03:32:45,301
The snow and slush that we got yesterday was very heavy, obviously, and it's

2542
03:32:45,654 --> 03:32:49,996
creating, I guarantee it's creating even more damage than there was a month ago.

2543
03:32:50,016 --> 03:32:52,397
It's unacceptable.

2544
03:32:52,597 --> 03:32:59,981
I know we discussed short-term and long-term goals for the library, but that library needs a new roof, and it should be done immediately.

2545
03:33:01,582 --> 03:33:03,383
My daughter asked, what is the dripping?

2546
03:33:03,863 --> 03:33:05,364
And I was just embarrassed.

2547
03:33:07,425 --> 03:33:08,605
And it's just unfortunate.

2548
03:33:08,726 --> 03:33:13,688
Motion to send that on to the DPW, the mayor's office for Councilor Knight.

2549
03:33:14,300 --> 03:33:18,803
Motion to amend the paper, Mr. President, to request an update on the selection process of a new library director.

2550
03:33:20,485 --> 03:33:21,165
We can amend that.

2551
03:33:24,167 --> 03:33:29,091
On the update, if you could put up the- Mr. Boutilier retired.

2552
03:33:29,111 --> 03:33:30,432
There's a vacancy right now.

2553
03:33:30,472 --> 03:33:31,513
The vacancy of the library.

2554
03:33:33,618 --> 03:33:41,042
And for your ratification, I have spoken with the mayor about bringing the library building commission to MedFed, and she is in favor of it.

2555
03:33:41,062 --> 03:33:50,626
And we're in the process of trying to set up something in the next couple weeks to bring to the MedFed to hopefully get some money for the library, which is available through the state.

2556
03:33:52,427 --> 03:33:56,809
I think that's great, and I think the library needs rehab.

2557
03:33:56,829 --> 03:34:02,292
I mean, I'm usually just in the children's section, maybe some romantic novels, just to clear my head at night.

2558
03:34:03,657 --> 03:34:08,141
In the children's section, I mean, there's chairs, they're ripping, they're falling apart.

2559
03:34:08,161 --> 03:34:13,666
I mean, we just need a revamp from chairs, tables, rugs.

2560
03:34:13,966 --> 03:34:18,970
I mean, whether we gut it, whether we add a second floor, we need to have a plan.

2561
03:34:19,431 --> 03:34:23,074
I'm begging the administration to let us know what her plan is.

2562
03:34:23,094 --> 03:34:26,477
I would actually maybe amend this to have a committee of the whole meeting.

2563
03:34:26,853 --> 03:34:30,295
to invite the mayor to discuss it so we know where we're going forward.

2564
03:34:30,315 --> 03:34:36,338
I think the roof needs to be done before our committee of the whole because next week, obviously, is going to be about charter review.

2565
03:34:36,918 --> 03:34:38,499
But that roof needs to be done.

2566
03:34:38,739 --> 03:34:42,181
And we cannot wait for any other outside funding, state funding.

2567
03:34:42,261 --> 03:34:49,725
That roof needs to be fixed before the roof comes crashing down and we ruin the whole children's section, or even possibly more.

2568
03:34:50,420 --> 03:34:54,184
So I know one of us should advocate for this every week.

2569
03:34:54,204 --> 03:34:55,705
We should bring it up every week.

2570
03:34:55,785 --> 03:34:58,808
I mean, it should be brought up every day with a leaky roof.

2571
03:34:59,468 --> 03:35:00,089
Unbelievable.

2572
03:35:00,709 --> 03:35:01,050
Thank you.

2573
03:35:01,230 --> 03:35:03,832
If we could send that to the mayor for her immediate attention, Mr. Clark.

2574
03:35:07,836 --> 03:35:08,957
Roll call has been requested.

2575
03:35:08,977 --> 03:35:11,119
As amended.

2576
03:35:24,515 --> 03:35:27,116
Yes, a motion of six in the affirmative, one absent.

2577
03:35:27,196 --> 03:35:27,896
Motion passes.

